go ahead :)<br><br><div><span class="gmail_quote">On 10/7/08, <b class="gmail_sendername">Pavel Shamis (Pasha)</b> &lt;<a href="mailto:pasha@dev.mellanox.co.il">pasha@dev.mellanox.co.il</a>&gt; wrote:</span><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0;margin-left:0.8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">
Hi,<br>
<br>
I would like to remove the btl_openib_ib_pkey_ix (btl_openib_ib_pkey_ix) parameter.<br>
The partition key index (btl_openib_ib_pkey_ix) is defined locally by each HCA, so in most cases each host will have different pkey index and<br>
user have no control over this value. So direct pkey_ix specification is not possible because each HCA will have different value.<br>
If user want to use specific partition he should specify only the btl_openib_ibib_pkey_val parameter, and Open-mpi translate it to corresponding pkey_ix.<br>
<br>
I think the btl_openib_ib_pkey_ix is useless and I would like to remove it.<br>
<br>
Comments ?<br><span class="sg">
